The main story line was pretty good, but it's very personal tone felt out of place with the rest of the games "bigger picture" focus. It also felt like they could have done a lot more with the settlement system. The quests were mostly generic with boring rewards, and there didn't feel like there was a lot of cool loot to discover. I did like the modding system for equipment though. I also wish your companion was more involved, because they felt like side notes after their main story was done.
